The paper deals with learning graphical models from distributed data, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also addresses communication constraints, which is a topic in "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of Gaussian graphical models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves information theory and communication efficiency, which are topics in "cs.IT" (Information Theory).
